  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 23:02 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC leader-long held and SOL bearish count confirmed\n\n**Task:** Re-scan HL top-trader copy intelligence after the P4 risk-easing shift and verify whether BTC leader-long alignment held or rotated into distribution.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 7L/0S**, **ETH 3L/5S**, **SOL 1L/7S**.\n- Current top-book notional:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$12.91M** vs shorts **$0.00M** \u2192 net **+$12.91M long**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.12M** vs shorts **$38.21M** \u2192 net **-$38.09M short**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.19M** vs shorts **$11.56M** \u2192 net **-$11.37M short**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.61M** vs shorts **$11.89M** \u2192 net **-$10.29M short**\n- BTC remains clean: **7 longs, 0 shorts**.\n- BTC notional dipped from the 22:42 scan (**$13.17M -> $12.91M**, about **-$0.26M / -2.0%**), but this is not meaningful distribution.\n- The top BTC block is intact: `anon-0xfc66` still **BTC LONG $5.63M**, `anon-0xecb6` trimmed **$4.93M -> $4.48M**, `anon-0x57dd` added **$2.16M -> $2.25M**, and `beatmaker1@proton.me` added **$0.15M -> $0.27M**.\n- ETH remains the strongest bearish expression by notional, led by `anon-0xecb6` **ETH SHORT $22.64M** and `anon-0xfc66` **ETH SHORT $13.44M**.\n- SOL shifted from count-neutral (**4L/4S**) to explicitly bearish by count and size (**1L/7S**, net **-$11.37M**), removing prior ambiguity.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-long-holds-sol-bearish-confirmation-2026-05-02-2302.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The risk-easing alpha shift did not trigger BTC leader distribution. BTC is still the clean copy-intel long and no top-20 BTC short reopened. SOL is the real change: the count now agrees with the bearish notional.\n\n**Decision:** Keep **BTC = clean bullish copy-intel leader**. Keep **ET